<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-128-754  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 128 754.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Feb 5 1990 n286 p74(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Aristacom, ATandamp;T target telemarketers. (SCIL-Link communicationssoftware) (Aristacom International Inc.) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Roeckl, Chris.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Aristacom International Inc and AT and T introduce two versions ofan integrated voice-data software package designed to enhancegateway interfaces in telemarketing applications.andP;  Knowngenerically as the Switch Computer Interface Link under theAristacom label, the communications software is designed toexchange information with the AT and T Definity CommunicationsSystem PBX and the IBM/370 mainframe computer.andP;  The respectiveversions are the SCIL*IG, designed for use with integratedservices digital network gateways, and the SCIL*ITG, designed foruse with integrated telemarketing gateways.andP;  The SCIL*IG workswith customer premises equipment to provide incomingcall-processing.andP;  SCIL*ITG offers the same functions in additionto automated outbound call processing.andP;  The software, available inMarch 1990, will run from $1,500 to $2,500 depending on systemconfiguration.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Aristacom International Inc. (product introduction)American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Product:   SCIL*IG (Telephone management software) (product introduction)SCIL*ITG (Telephone management software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCommunications Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>